According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Military Disinformation Tracking (Social Media) OSINT Platform Market was valued at USD 2.15 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 2.68 billion in 2026 to USD 12.45 billion by 2034, registering a remarkable CAGR of 21.2% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing rapid expansion as defense and intelligence agencies increasingly invest in advanced open-source intelligence (OSINT) platforms to detect, analyze, and counter sophisticated disinformation campaigns across social media. Growing geopolitical tensions, hybrid warfare strategies, and AI-powered influence operations are driving demand for real-time monitoring, multilingual analysis, and automated threat detection solutions.
